Think a little. Have your own mind. Laugh when you want to laugh. If you hate the parody, say it, but stop pretending to get offended over something you know nothing about just to seem like an angel. text: Don't have a clue about the rest of the movie, but I think the reason they stay on Skype instead of just leaving or turning off their computers is because someone is killed or tortured every time they try that. It's like the villain behind all of it is saying "Keep talking to me and playing my games, or die". They did the same thing in Scream when Ghostface threatens to kill his victims if they keep hanging up on him (even though he does that anyway). As for other things that would be common sense to do in this situation (calling the cops, getting the parents, etc.), I'm pretty sure the characters aren't so stupid that they wouldn't have tried all of that. Just because it's not in the trailer doesn't necessarily mean they never attempt it. Personally, I think people often take trailers too seriously, some of what they show doesn't even translate to the actual movie anymore. The film as a whole is just a metaphor for the dangers of social networking, cyber bullying, and most clearly, cyber stalking. Though crimes like that do happen more commonly than we think in real life, this obviously takes it over the top. It's basically Pulse + I know What You Did Last Summer + Paranormal Activity, but I'll give it a chance anyway. At least it seems fairly more original than half the crap studios churn out in horror flicks these days. I for one plan on doing my best to make every story I write try to stand out.

text: I'm sorry for those that happen to be reading the comments without actually having seen the movie first, but it's your own fault. If you don't want any possible spoilers, read no further. The aspect regarding "just turn off your Skype" in this parody and some of the people in the comments that are coming up with invalid solutions they thought the characters in the movie could have acted upon just pisses me off. First of all they COULDN'T turn off their Skype because the ghost of Laura Barns said if they turn off their Skype or leave the call they die. It could even control all of their computers so it's easily possible for it to force them to stay in the call. If they turned off their video they would die, or the ghost would just force it back on like it forced all of their mics off of mute. If they tried turning off their computers they would die. If they tried to leave their houses to meet in a public place they would get killed before they could even leave their house. The only solution would have been to not cyber bully Laura Barns in the first place. They did the wrong thing, on top of many other wrong things, and they had to face the consequences. To everyone here and to the ones who made this parody video: Make sure you KNOW what you're talking about before making a video on it or typing a comment. With all that said, I enjoyed the parody, despite the "turn off Skype" aspect of it.
